<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</emphasis>
Single specimen (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 57" captionStartId="F57" captionText="Figure 57. Euplectellinae stet. CCZ _ 199 A in situ image B detail of body C whole specimen with protruding basalia. Scale bars: 1 cm (A); 5 mm (B). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (B, C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure57" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716383" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">57A</figureCitation>
). Lophophytous white sponge with tubular habitus (L = 5 cm). There is a large, central osculum (d = 2cm), and protruding fistules with terminal suboscula, each with one or two, mostly two, openings (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 57" captionStartId="F57" captionText="Figure 57. Euplectellinae stet. CCZ _ 199 A in situ image B detail of body C whole specimen with protruding basalia. Scale bars: 1 cm (A); 5 mm (B). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (B, C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure57" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716383" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">57B</figureCitation>
). Long basalia (L = 6 cm) arranged as a tube, protruding from the lower end of the habitus and anchored to the sediment (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 57" captionStartId="F57" captionText="Figure 57. Euplectellinae stet. CCZ _ 199 A in situ image B detail of body C whole specimen with protruding basalia. Scale bars: 1 cm (A); 5 mm (B). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (B, C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure57" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716383" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">57C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
